I also tried experimenting with whether the episode was a special occasion, what day of the week the episode was released on, and how many guests were on the episode. On my first pass, I didn't find any of those variables to be significant predictors of whether an episode was Best Of'd.

The things you'll want to pay attention to in the table are probably the lm_weight column. It suggests that a basic episode, with none of the top 29 guests, has approximately a 13% chance of being Best Of'd. PFT adds 23%, meaning that an episode with only Paul and Scott has a 36% chance of being Best Of'd. If Nick Kroll shows up to the recording, we're up to over 50%.

Using only the guests who correlate very well with Best Of'd episodes, we can attempt to make the most Best Of-y lineup possible: 

**Paul F. Tompkins, Lauren Lapkus, Nick Kroll, Jason Mantzoukas, Andy Daly, and Ben Schwartz**
